The paper deals with lower bounds for graph problems in the streaming model of computation and query complexity, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of communication complexity and direct-sum arguments suggests a connection to cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with sub-modular minimization, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper presents new multi-pass space lower bounds in turnstile streams, which is a specific type of streaming model, suggesting a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
